<h2 id="comments">Comments</h2>

<div id="c1">
<p>The Sidekick was fantastic. I was an over-enthusiastic fan since the day they came out and used Sidekicks for about 3-4 years. In my opinion, the problem with their demise wasn&#8217;t their fault, it was T-Mobile&#8217;s. Danger wanted to continue developing a kick-ass device and T-Mobile wanted to make the device hip to the hip hop crowd and ballers. One would think you could have both but the features in later models were driven more by T-Mobile and T-Mobile would actually suppress features that were available on the Hiptop in other markets.</p>

<p>It was no surprise that Andy Rubin and others left Danger to start Android.</p>

