<p>I owned both the sidekick 2 and 3. They <em>were</em> great machines, I loved being able use AIM, and the keyboard was amazing. However for me there were a few things that really killed it for me:</p>

<ol>
<li><p>size and form factor. Sorry, the freaking thing was huge and beefy. For those of us without purses, it was a PITA.</p></li>
<li><p>Media player &#8230; personally I like listening to music and I like carrying only one device. It&#8217;s just way easier on the iPhone.</p></li>
</ol>

<p>With regards to the keyboard &#8230; when the iPhone does let you use the keyboard in landscape mode (which is exceedingly rare), it&#8217;s actually not that bad. There&#8217;s definitely a rabid group of iPhone users out there who are clamoring and praying for expanded use of the landscape mode.</p>

