<div id="c22">
<p>Steve said: &#8220;Hell, everyone thinks MS stole the mouse idea from Apple but Apple stole it from Xerox PARC.&#8221;</p>

<p>The mouse was not invented by Xerox, but by Douglas Engelbart, who presented it in 1968. Xerox came up with several other ideas which Apple licensed (not stole) from Xerox. Apple also added a bunch of significant ideas to the Mac OS which had never been done before.</p>

<p>Overall, if you look at the UI of the original Mac, it was probably 1/3 from Engelbart and other early inventors, 1/3 from Xerox, and 1/3 from Apple.</p>

<p>Here&#8217;s a popular story article on this subject:
http://www.folklore.org/StoryView.py?project=Macintosh&amp;story=On_Xerox,_Apple_and_Progress.txt</p>

<p class="posted">posted by Tom Ross
 on December 12, 2008 <a href="forgottensidekick#c22" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
